net.proteusframework.core.hibernate

Class DelegatingHibernateInterceptor

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.core.hibernate.DelegatingHibernateInterceptor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Interceptor

    public abstract class DelegatingHibernateInterceptor
extends Object
implements Interceptor

    A hibernate interceptor base class that allows a user to delegate to a delegate interceptor. If the delegate interceptor is not set, either through DelegatingHibernateInterceptor(Interceptor), or setDelegateInterceptor(Interceptor), this base class will behave identically to EmptyInterceptor.

    For this reason, it is recommended that all custom interceptors extend this class as opposed to EmptyInterceptor as it provides the ability to delegate to another Interceptor (and only if desired).

    It is also highly recommended that you configure a hibernate interceptor chain through Spring using a chain of DelegatingHibernateInterceptors.

    Author:
    Kevin Beaty (kbeaty@i2rd.com)
